This Python script is a simple expense tracker that allows users to manage their expenses using a CSV file. It provides the following functionalities:

Add Expense – Users can input a date, category, and amount, which gets saved in expenses.csv.

View Expenses – Displays all recorded expenses in a formatted list.

Delete Expense – Allows users to remove an expense by selecting its number.

Show Most Expensive Expense – Finds and displays the highest expense recorded.

Show Total by Category – Summarizes total spending per category.

Menu Interface – Users interact via a simple menu to choose actions.